Reasoning: The paper discusses the application of Integer Linear Programming (ILP) in various areas of artificial intelligence, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also introduces a new structural measure called fracture backdoors, which could fall under the cs.DS sub-category. The development of exact and approximation algorithms for computing fracture backdoors suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CC sub-category. The parameterized algorithms for ILP and the matching lower bounds could fall under the cs.LG sub-category. Finally, the study of the complexity landscape of ILP with respect to fracture backdoors could also belong to the cs.DM sub-category.
